              "と",
              "先週",
              "海",
              "に",
              "行きました"
            ]
          ],
          "explanation": "と marks the companion ('with a friend'). に marks the destination. 先週 (last week) can float before or after the topic."
        },
        {
          "q": "Leg 2: I wanted to eat delicious fish there.",
          "segments": [
            "そこ",
            "で",
            "おいしい",
            "魚",
            "を",
            "食べたかった",
            "です"
          ],
          "distractors": [
            "に",
            "食べたい",
            "食べて"
          ],
          "explanation": "〜たかったです is the past form of 〜たいです (desire). で marks the location of the action. おいしい directly modifies 魚 as an attributive adjective."
        },
        {
          "q": "Leg 3: We walked on the beach, sang songs, and did other things.",
          "segments": [
            "歩いたり",
            "歌ったり",
            "しました"
          ],
          "distractors": [
            "歩いて",
            "歌って",
            "します"
          ],
          "explanation": "〜たり〜たりする lists representative actions ('did things like ~'). 歩く (godan) → 歩いたり, 歌う (godan) → 歌ったり. しました closes the pattern. Distractors 歩いて / 歌って are て-form connectors — similar but wrong pattern."
        },
        {
          "q": "Leg 4: From the sea, we could see a beautiful mountain.",
          "segments": [
            "海",
            "から",
            "きれいな",
            "山",
            "が",
            "見えました"
          ],
          "distractors": [
            "を",
            "に",
            "見ました"
          ],
          "explanation": "見える (to be visible) is an intransitive potential — the mountain is visible, not 'I saw it'. が marks the subject of visibility. きれいな is a な-adjective modifying 山. The distractor 見ました (saw) would need を, not が."
        },
        {
          "q": "Leg 5: If the weather is good tomorrow, let's go again.",
          "segments": [
            "明日",
            "天気",
            "が",
            "よかったら",
            "また",
            "行きましょう"
          ],
          "distractors": [
            "は",
            "よければ",
            "行きたい"
